label.value: Absent in utero ossification of vertebral bodies

definition.value: A developmental defect of the sacrum characterized by partial or disordered development of the sacrum in which portions of the sacrum, which normally is formed by fusion of five sacral vertebrae S1-S5, fail to form or fail to form normally.

label.value: Absent spinous processes of lower thoracic and lumbar vertebrae

definition.value: An abnormality related to a defect of vertebral separation of sacral vertebrae during development.
